  "body": "- [x] I've asked for help in the [Truffle Gitter](http://gitter.im/Consensys/truffle) before filing this issue.\r\n\r\n---------------------------\r\n\r\n## Issue\r\n\r\nI want to debug a transaction after tests has run. But when I want to step into a particular function pressing \"i\" for \"step into\", the debugger process hangs after printed \"...Stepping\" into the console.\r\nAlthough I have waited many minutes, nothing else happened. \r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n\r\nRunning tests:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntruffle test\r\n```\r\n\r\nOne test will raise an revert I want to debug it:\r\n\r\n```\r\ntruffle debug $transaction\r\n```\r\n\r\nwhere $transation is the particular transaction-id that I have found in the ganache-log.\r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\n\r\nThat I can step into the function with a hanging \"Stepping\"-process.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\n\r\nIt hangs with \"Stepping\".\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n* Operating System: \r\n\r\nMacOS Mojave\r\n\r\n$ truffle version\r\nTruffle v5.0.20 (core: 5.0.20)\r\nSolidity v0.5.0 (solc-js)\r\nNode v10.16.0\r\nWeb3.js v1.0.0-beta.37\r\nnpm: 6.9.0\r\n\r\n\r\n",
